arms.name: Ontamalimab 75 mg

objectives.name: Primary Safety Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the safety and tolerability of ontamalimab 75 mg in participants with nonalcoholic steatohepatitis (NASH) and liver fibrosis

objectives.name: Secondary Biomarker Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of ontamalimab on biomarkers and noninvasive tests in participants with NASH and liver fibrosis

objectives.name: Exploratory Biomarker Objective
objectives.text: To explore additional biomarkers and noninvasive test assessments

objectives.name: Pharmacokinetic Objective
objectives.text: To characterize the pharmacokinetics of ontamalimab in participants with NASH and liver fibrosis

endpoints.name: Treatment-Emergent Adverse Events

endpoints.name: Pro-C3 Change from Baseline
endpoints.text: Percent change from baseline in Pro-C3 at Week 24 analyzed using a mixed effects model for repeated measure (MMRM)

endpoints.name: ELF Change from Baseline
endpoints.text: Percent change from baseline in Enhanced Liver Fibrosis (ELF) score at Week 24 analyzed using a mixed effects model for repeated measure (MMRM)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Biomarkers and Noninvasive Tests

notes.text: a. Visits 4a, 4a2, and 4b comprise the baseline visit. Visits 4a and 4b are required for all participants; Visit 4a2 (abdominal MRI only) is optional for participants with historical qualifying liver biopsy. Footnote for Schedule of Activities tables: When the same visit window date is used for both screening and baseline visits, all screening assessments must be completed before the baseline assessments.
b. For early termination visits: All EOS assessments should be completed at the early termination visit, and safety follow-up assessments should occur 12 weeks after the last dose of study drug.
c. Perform at Visit 10 (Week 24) only if not previously done at an earlier visit.
d. Assessments at Visit 10 (Week 24) can be done at Week 20 visit if participant discontinues early.
e. At Week 24, liver biopsy is required unless medically contraindicated.
f. May be collected at unscheduled visits.
h. For female participants of childbearing potential only.
j. At Week 36 or at early termination.
l. PK sample to be collected predose.
m. ADA/NAb sample to be collected predose.
n. Circulating inflammatory cells sample to be collected predose.
o. Can be performed up to 1 year before screening.
q. For participants who test positive for SARS-CoV-2 at screening.

studyAmendments.summary: No summary available in the provided document.

The overall reasons for this protocol amendment are to: Revise inclusion and exclusion criteria to improve feasibility of study conduct at a variety of clinical sites. Clarify contraception methods for male study participants and for female sexual partners of male participants. Add an additional part to the baseline visit to allow confirmation of eligibility on the basis of liver chemistry tests before dosing. Clarify acceptable conditions for repeating screening laboratory samples. Allow flexibility to perform Week -6 and Week 24 assessments on different days within the specified visit window.

The overall reasons for this protocol amendment are to: Revise inclusion and exclusion criteria to improve study feasibility. Clarify the screening period eligibility and extension of its duration. Clarify the acceptable conditions for including severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus-2 (SARS-CoV-2)-infected participants into the study and to allow adequate time for recovery of symptoms before screening.

conditions.text: ELF score 7.7 at Week -8 (SV1)

conditions.name: NASH Histological Criteria
conditions.text: NAS 3 with at least 1 point in lobular inflammation

conditions.name: Fibrosis Stage Eligibility
conditions.text: Liver fibrosis stage F1 through F4cc according to NASH CRN

conditions.name: F4cc Fibrosis Criteria
conditions.description: Non-invasive criteria for F4 compensated cirrhosis
conditions.text: FIB-4 3.48 and LSM 20 kPa or Agile 4 score 0.57

conditions.name: AST Exclusion Threshold
conditions.text: AST levels >5ULN

conditions.name: ALT Exclusion Threshold
conditions.text: ALT levels >5ULN

conditions.name: ALP Exclusion Threshold
conditions.text: ALP 2ULN

conditions.name: Serum Creatinine Exclusion
conditions.text: Serum creatinine 1.5ULN or eGFR <45 mL/min/1.73 m2

conditions.name: INR Exclusion Threshold
conditions.text: INR 1.3 (except for participants receiving anticoagulant treatment)

conditions.name: Total Bilirubin Exclusion
conditions.text: TBL ULN (except for Gilbert's syndrome with normal direct bilirubin)

conditions.name: Direct Bilirubin Exclusion
conditions.text: Direct bilirubin 3ULN

conditions.name: Platelet Count Exclusion
conditions.text: Platelet count <6010^9/L

conditions.name: Decompensated Liver Disease
conditions.text: Presence or history of ascites, hepatic encephalopathy, or variceal bleeding

conditions.name: Child-Pugh Score Exclusion
conditions.text: Child-Pugh >6 (Class B or C), unless due to therapeutic anticoagulation

conditions.name: MELD Score Exclusion
conditions.text: MELD score >12

conditions.name: F4cc Safety Clearance
conditions.text: Safety and tolerability established in first four noncirrhotic (F1-F3) participants who have received at least 3 doses of ontamalimab 75 mg and have been monitored for at least 12 weeks after the first dose

conditions.name: Age Eligibility

conditions.name: Positive IGRA Management

conditions.text: If both initial and confirmatory IGRA results are indeterminate, participant may be enrolled after negative Mantoux tuberculin skin test and consultation with specialist determining low risk of infection

transitionRules.name: Screening to Liver Biopsy Transition
transitionRules.text: Participants with Pro-C3 12.6 ng/mL and ELF score 7.7 who meet inclusion criteria and none of exclusion criteria at SV1 will be eligible for liver biopsy at SV2

transitionRules.name: Screening to Treatment Transition
transitionRules.text: Indication for NASH (NAS 3 with at least 1 point in lobular inflammation) and liver fibrosis stage F1 through F4cc in the liver biopsy will enable participants to enroll in the study

transitionRules.name: F4cc Enrollment Gate
transitionRules.text: After safety and tolerability have been established in the first four noncirrhotic (F1-F3) participants who have received at least 3 doses of ontamalimab 75 mg and have been monitored for at least 12 weeks after the first dose, eligible F4cc participants will be allowed to enroll

transitionRules.name: Treatment to Follow-up Transition
transitionRules.text: All participants, including those who discontinue, will undergo a safety follow-up period through 12 weeks after the last dose of study drug

transitionRules.name: Liver Chemistry Stopping Rule
transitionRules.text: Liver chemistry stopping criteria per algorithm for study drug discontinuation

transitionRules.name: PML Symptom Discontinuation
transitionRules.text: Any unexplained symptoms suggestive of progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy (PML) based on targeted neurological assessment

transitionRules.name: SARS-CoV-2 Screening Pause
transitionRules.text: In case of positive test for SARS-CoV-2 infection, screening may be paused for an additional 2 weeks

transitionRules.name: Screen Failure to Rescreen
transitionRules.text: An individual who has been designated a screen failure may be rescreened once

transitionRules.name: Decompensation Discontinuation
transitionRules.text: New signs of decompensation and/or clinically meaningful change in disease status including presence of ascites, hepatic encephalopathy, or variceal bleeding

commentAnnotations.text: Maximum allowed time between historical liver biopsy and first dose of study drug is 34 weeks for any participant, except for the participants who test positive for SARS-CoV-2 at screening
Progression of screening is contingent on successful confirmation of eligibility along with the sponsor's approval
In case of positive test for SARS-CoV-2 infection, screening may be paused for an additional 2 weeks (ie, screening period of up to 12 weeks)

The screening period can be extended by 2 weeks for any reason (including but not limited to a repeat test requirement for select and predefined measurements) on a case-by-case basis with the sponsor's approval
An individual who has been designated a screen failure may be rescreened once
Not more than four participants with F1 fibrosis will be enrolled in this study

An adverse event (AE) is defined as any untoward medical occurrence in a clinical investigation participant who has signed informed consent to participate in a study; it does not necessarily have to have a causal relationship with the treatment
Samples for immunogenicity should be collected when worsening of a disease is reported as an AE

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: Global amendment to revise inclusion and exclusion criteria to improve study feasibility, clarify screening period eligibility and extension of its duration, and clarify acceptable conditions for including SARS-CoV-2-infected participants

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Revised title to change fibrosis stages from 'F2 Through F4' to 'F1 Through F4'
Multiple clarifications including fibrosis stage definitions, NASH indication terminology, dosing schedule clarification, and screening period requirements
Removed Inclusion Criterion #4 (FAST Score), revised Criterion #6 to lower NAS requirement from 4 to 3 and fibrosis stage from F2 to F1
Revised Exclusion Criteria #1, #2, #6a, #7, #17, #21, #25, #26 including removal of SARS-CoV-2 infection criterion
Added statements related to screening period extension, SARS-CoV-2 testing requirements, and rescreening allowances
Added cap of four participants with F1 fibrosis enrollment
Restructured tables, added new Table 2 for Visit 4a and 4a2, revised footnotes and column structure
Added definition statement for adverse events and new subsection for pretreatment-emergent adverse events
Removed 'dose increased' and 'dose reduced' from Action Taken options
Removed 4-week waiting period requirement for rescreening
Added instruction for immunogenicity sample collection when worsening of disease is reported as AE

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: Revise inclusion and exclusion criteria to improve study feasibility
Clarify the screening period eligibility and extension of its duration
Clarify the acceptable conditions for including SARS-CoV-2-infected participants into the study and to allow adequate time for recovery of symptoms before screening
Clarification of terminology and procedures throughout protocol
To have a wider and diverse range of participants from all fibrosis stages (F1 through F4cc) enrolled in the study
To improve study feasibility by expanding the study inclusion parameters while maintaining a population that is optimal for assessing the anti-inflammatory/anti-fibrogenic mechanism of this drug
NAS 4 to NAS 3 to reduce screen failures on NAS subscores due to nonreliability of the ballooning score
To improve study feasibility, recognizing the study population to be enrolled (HbA1c requirement change)
To correct the list of possible actions that can be taken in response to an adverse event, given that a single dose of ontamalimab (75 mg) is available for use in this study
To allow participants to rescreen on a case-by-case basis after discussion with the investigator
To clarify the instructions for collection of samples for immunogenicity in case of worsening of a disease being reported as an AE
